SetUp

public com.treestar.lib.xml.SElement SetUp(java.util.List<java.util.List<java.awt.Point>> vals,
                                           com.treestar.lib.xml.SElement fcmlElem,
                                           java.lang.String fXParm,
                                           java.lang.String fYParm)
Function takes gate-set points, parent elemen, and parmeters. It then constructs a Gating-ML element based on these points and passes this object into the compute function. Compute function computes population count inbetween gate set defined in XML and returns it as an integer. This integer is then divides the parent population's count producing a percentage. The percentage is compared to the parents and kept if it is reasonable close to it. The function iterates through all gate sets and returns the best fitting one.

Parameters:
vals -
fcmlElem -
fXParm -
fYParm -
